# Build-context hygiene for the frontend image.
#
# Without this file, `COPY . .` in the builder stage pulled in the
# host's `.next/` (10MB+ of cached compile artifacts) and
# `node_modules/` (hundreds of MB). `node_modules` was harmless because
# `COPY --from=deps` immediately replaced it, but `.next/` carried
# forward into the builder layer and made every build slower than it
# needed to be, leaked host state into the image, and made layer
# caching nondeterministic across machines. Excluding it here keeps the
# build hermetic.
#
# Anything listed here is excluded from the build context that Docker
# sends to the daemon. It does not affect host files.

# Generated artifacts
.next
out
build
dist
.turbo

# Dependencies (installed inside the builder by Stage 1)
node_modules

# Source control + IDE
.git
.gitignore
.vscode
.idea

# Native build outputs (these come from Capacitor, not the web image)
android
ios
android-config
ios-config

# Test + lint artifacts
coverage
playwright-report
test-results
.eslintcache
.lighthouserc.json

# Editor and OS scratch
*.log
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Environment files belong outside the image; values come in via
# docker-compose env_file or build ARGs at runtime.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Local dev compose override (we add docker-compose.override.yml at
# repo root, not inside frontend/, but list it defensively).
docker-compose.override.yml
